Set Up a React Project
If you already have a React app, skip this step.
Otherwise, create a new React project:
sh
Copy
Edit
npx create-react-app lead-workflow-builder --template cra-template
cd lead-workflow-builder
3️⃣ Install Required Dependencies
Inside your project directory, install the necessary libraries:

sh
Copy
Edit
npm install reactflow lucide-react @radix-ui/react-select
4️⃣ Replace Code in src/LeadWorkflowBuilder.js
Create a new file LeadWorkflowBuilder.js inside src/
Copy and paste the updated code that I will provide.
5️⃣ Use the Component in App.js
Replace the contents of src/App.js with:

jsx
Copy
Edit
import React from "react";
import LeadWorkflowBuilder from "./LeadWorkflowBuilder";

function App() {
  return (
    <div className="App">
      <LeadWorkflowBuilder />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
6️⃣ Start the Development Server
sh
Copy
Edit
npm start
Your app should now be running at http://localhost:3000.








How to run this locally:
Ensure you have Node.js installed (preferably v18+).
Create a new React project if not already done:
sh
Copy
Edit
npx create-react-app my-app --template typescript
cd my-app
Install required dependencies:
sh
Copy
Edit
npm install reactflow lucide-react @radix-ui/react-select
Replace App.tsx (or an appropriate component file) with the updated code.
Start the development server:
sh
Copy
Edit
npm start







